name: SNOMEDCTCOREProblemList
title: SNOMED CT CORE Problem List
description: This expansion set contains only SNOMED CT codes and names.  To view the entire set of attributes, full inclusion and exclusion rules, and details on the methodology that was used to create the SNOMED CT CORE Problem List subset, go to https://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/Snomed/core_subset.html
purpose:
(Clinical Focus: Concepts from the NLM SNOMED CT Clinical Observations Recordings and Encodings (CORE) Problem List subset are included in this value set.  The main purpose of the NLM SNOMED CT CORE Problem List subset is to define a UMLS subset that is most useful for documenting and encoding clinical content information at the summary level.  The CORE Problem List subset includes SNOMED CT concepts and codes that can be used for the problem list, discharge diagnoses, or reason of encounter.),(Data Element Scope: The file identifies a useful subset of SNOMED CT, but does not include all the information likely to be required to make effective use of SNOMED CT in an application, such as synonyms that may include more clinician-friendly terms than the SNOMED CT fully-specified name. The identifiers in the file can be used to extract more complete information for these concepts from either the UMLS release files or the SNOMED CT native format files.),(Inclusion Criteria: Only active SNOMED CT concepts from the Clinical finding, Procedure, Situation with explicit context, and Events hierarchies are included.
Additionally, the following content are included in the CORE Problem List subset but not displayed in the value set, to see the following data (and definitions) see the native download: UMLS CUI, Occurrence, Usage, First in Subset, Is Retired From Subset, Last in Subset, Replaced by SNOMED CT ID.),(Exclusion Criteria: Inactive SNOMED CT concepts are removed from each new version of the CORE.)
